The paper deals with planar drawings of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves the study of graph embeddings and properties of graphs such as series-parallel and bipartite graphs, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the non-planarity of certain graphs, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.DS) and the impossibility of certain types of drawings, which is a topic in computer graphics (cs.SI).
